# CountryService

A Spring Boot microservice that fetches country data from the public [REST Countries v3.1 API](https://restcountries.com) and returns a clean, enriched response with business rules applied.

---

## What It Does

- Exposes a single endpoint: `GET /countries/{code}`
- Accepts any two-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-2 country code (e.g. `US`, `DE`, `IN`)
- Fetches live data from `https://restcountries.com/v3.1/alpha/{code}`
- Returns a simplified JSON response with a population-based size category

### Example

**Request:**
```
GET /countries/US
```

**Response:**
```json
{
  "countryCode": "US",
  "name": "United States of America",
  "capital": "Washington, D.C.",
  "region": "Americas",
  "currencies": ["USD"],
  "languages": ["English"],
  "borders": ["CAN", "MEX"],
  "sizeCategory": "LARGE"
}
```

---

## Size Category Rules

| Population | Category |
|---|---|
| Less than 1,000,000 | `SMALL` |
| 1,000,000 – 10,000,000 | `MEDIUM` |
| More than 10,000,000 | `LARGE` |

---

## Error Responses

| Scenario | HTTP Status |
|---|---|
| Code is not two letters (e.g. `USA`) | `400 Bad Request` |
| Country not found (e.g. `ZZ`) | `404 Not Found` |
| Upstream API unreachable | `502 Bad Gateway` |

---

## Requirements

- Java 17+
- Maven (or use the included `./mvnw` wrapper)

---

## How to Run

```bash
# 1. Clone the repo
git clone https://github.com/ginni-singn/CountryService.git
cd CountryService

# 2. Build
./mvnw clean package

# 3. Run
./mvnw spring-boot:run
```

The app starts on **http://localhost:8080**

---

## How to Test

```bash
./mvnw test
```

Tests include:
- **Unit tests** — business rules, mapping, validation, error cases
- **Integration tests** — full request/response cycle with WireMock (no real network calls)

---

## Try It Out

```bash
curl http://localhost:8080/countries/US
curl http://localhost:8080/countries/IN
curl http://localhost:8080/countries/MT   # island nation, no borders
curl http://localhost:8080/countries/USA  # → 400 Bad Request
```

---

## Project Structure

```
src/
├── main/java/com/countryservice/
│   ├── controller/     # HTTP layer (routing, status codes)
│   ├── service/        # Business logic and mapping
│   ├── model/          # Request/response DTOs
│   ├── exception/      # Custom exceptions + global error handler
│   └── config/         # Spring beans (RestTemplate)
└── test/java/com/countryservice/
    ├── controller/     # MockMvc slice tests
    ├── service/        # Unit tests
    └── integration/    # WireMock integration tests
```

---

## Design Decisions

- **RestTemplate is a Spring bean** (not `new`-ed inside the service) so it can be injected and mocked in tests
- **Layered architecture** — controller, service, model, and exception layers are clearly separated so new features (e.g. caching, new endpoints) can be added without touching unrelated code
- **Null-safe mapping** — all upstream fields are null-checked to prevent NPEs for edge cases like island nations (no borders) or countries with no listed capital
- **Externalised base URL** — the upstream API URL lives in `application.properties` so it can be overridden in tests or different environments without code changes
